 Three Hyperbaric Oxygen Treatments for Acute Carbon Monoxide Poisoning.

 All patients presenting with acute carbon monoxide poisoning will receive one hyperbaric oxygen treatment (barring contraindications for hyperbaric oxygen therapy).

 After this treatment, eligible patients who provide consent will be randomly allocated to receive two sham sessions, or two additional hyperbaric oxygen sessions administered in a double-blind fashion.

 Outcome measures will be administered at 6 weeks and 6 months.

